title: Having a directX issue out of no where which caused me to not be able to connect to a game.

embed.description: BEFORE SUBMITTING A TICKET, MAKE SURE YOU'VE VISITED OUR ALPHA CLIENT DISCUSSION AND ALPHA CLIENT BUGS BOARDS OR SUBMITTED A BUG REPORT IN THE CLIENT. THE LEAGUE CLIENT UPDATE TEAM IS ON THE LOOKOUT FOR BUG REPORTS AND FEEDBACK!

body:
I created a support ticket for this issue but that system is honestly really ... confusing. The only way to get to that page is with the link as my active tickets page links me to a blank page and i cant see anything i have attached to the ticket. I don't know if the ticket has actually worked or if its just bugged out.

Original Post now follows:

So I log in for a game today and while loading in I get the error "An unkown DirectX error has occurred and League of Legends cannot start."

I was qued for a ranked game so obviously I started to panic trying not to lose my precious LP this late in the season to some bs like this.

My first reaction was to see if my drivers on anything were not up to date which they were based on windows update for my integrated chip (even though i run on a GFX card) and to check my nvidia drivers which were also up to date.

Funny thing was that I manually install drivers every time so i know i was using the same config to play last night as i was today, the last game I played last night was a league game so there should of been no difference between my last league game and my most recent one.

I have fixed the issue anyways by reinstalling my nvidia drivers through GeForce but that was my last resort and it took so long the game was FF ed

I lost 17 lp for this which is not a huge hit, but i am much more concerned about my mmr and getting flagged by leaver buster as an afker for some strange bug I had no control over. Would it be possible to get this counted as a lose prevented in that regard even if i still lose LP.

Screen shots for relevant info are attached. I have been playing league for years and this is the first time something like this has happened.

Thanks,

Sagesfury
